- [chuckling]

224
00:14:26.291 --> 00:14:29.750
Oh. it's a pretty old track.
but I love it. Love it.

225
00:14:29.833 --> 00:14:31.000
Okay. I love it too.

226
00:14:31.083 --> 00:14:32.708
[chuckles] Okay.

227
00:14:33.291 --> 00:14:34.291
What is that?

228
00:14:34.333 --> 00:14:37.083
You should actually make me a playlist.
I need some of this.

229
00:14:37.166 --> 00:14:38.886
- Hey. Phila. Is that a fire?
- [song stops]

230
00:14:39.416 --> 00:14:40.416
[Phila] Where?

231
00:14:40.958 --> 00:14:42.166
[Zinhle] Can you see it?

232
00:14:43.416 --> 00:14:44.750
Shit! That's...

233
00:14:46.375 --> 00:14:48.875
[tense music playing]

234
00:14:57.541 --> 00:14:59.250
We should call the fire brigade.

235
00:14:59.333 --> 00:15:02.166
No. don't call anybody. okay.
Just stay right here.

236
00:15:03.666 --> 00:15:04.833
Stay in the car.

237
00:15:06.458 --> 00:15:08.291
Zinhle. stay in the car!

238
00:15:11.500 --> 00:15:13.208
[fire crackling]

239
00:15:13.291 --> 00:15:15.416
Hey. Hey. Hey!

240
00:15:16.416 --> 00:15:18.333
[in Zulu] Hey! Wake up!

241
00:15:18.958 --> 00:15:20.333
[in English] Get up. Get up.

242
00:15:20.416 --> 00:15:21.416
Get up!

243
00:15:21.958 --> 00:15:23.208
What happened?

244
00:15:23.291 --> 00:15:25.250
[Zinhle] Yeah. has Angela left yet?

245
00:15:25.333 --> 00:15:26.666
[indistinct talking on phone]

246
00:15:26.750 --> 00:15:28.791
[Zinhle]
Phila Bhengu is at the Yellowvate factory.

247
00:15:28.875 --> 00:15:30.708
[guard in Zulu] The stock is on fire.

248
00:15:30.791 --> 00:15:32.017
- [in English] What?
- The stock!

249
00:15:32.041 --> 00:15:33.500
Get the truck. we're going inside!

250
00:15:37.416 --> 00:15:38.666
Oh. Jesus!

251
00:15:39.583 --> 00:15:42.041
[grunts. coughs]

252
00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:49.125
Jesus!

253
00:15:51.208 --> 00:15:52.208
[grunts]

254
00:15:53.041 --> 00:15:54.375
- [sizzles]
- Ah!

255
00:15:58.750 --> 00:15:59.958
[grunts]

256
00:16:02.375 --> 00:16:03.375
[grunts]

257
00:16:22.375 --> 00:16:23.875
Let's put them on the truck.

258
00:16:26.291 --> 00:16:27.458
[guard coughs]

259
00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:31.250
Phila! What is this?

260
00:16:31.750 --> 00:16:33.726
- Let me help you.
- I told you to stay in the car.

261
00:16:33.750 --> 00:16:34.750
Let me help.

262
00:16:45.791 --> 00:16:47.791
[fire truck siren wailing]

263
00:16:47.875 --> 00:16:49.208
What are you doing here?

264
00:16:49.291 --> 00:16:51.500
A burning building
is a news item. Mr. Bhengu.

265
00:16:51.583 --> 00:16:54.041
What are you doing here?
Is this a Bhengu factory?

266
00:16:54.125 --> 00:16:55.445
This is a private property. okay.

267
00:16:55.500 --> 00:16:58.083
So it is a Bhengu factory.
What's in the boxes?

268
00:16:59.375 --> 00:17:00.416
- Look. you...
- Phila...

269
00:17:03.958 --> 00:17:07.041
[Angela] Does that say
Yellowvate Skin Lightening. Mr. Bhengu?

270
00:17:11.333 --> 00:17:12.458
Mr. Bhengu?

271
00:17:12.541 --> 00:17:14.458
[sirens blaring]

272
00:17:24.583 --> 00:17:26.000
[Phila sighs]

273
00:17:30.041 --> 00:17:32.083
I am sorry. okay. I am so sorry.

274
00:17:32.166 --> 00:17:33.966
[in Xhosa]
What were you doing at the factory?

275
00:17:34.000 --> 00:17:35.226
Zinhle and I were at a party...

276
00:17:35.250 --> 00:17:37.750
Don't tell me about Zinhle.
What were you doing at the factory?

277
00:17:37.833 --> 00:17:38.913
What are you talking about?

278
00:17:38.958 --> 00:17:40.878
[in English] Ndu. inside.
Zinhle. to the cottage.

279
00:17:40.916 --> 00:17:42.458
[in Xhosa] Mom. what is going on here?

280
00:17:42.541 --> 00:17:44.301
[in English]
Do you realize what you've done?

281
00:17:44.333 --> 00:17:46.208
- What was I supposed to do?
- Really?

282
00:17:46.291 --> 00:17:48.083
Can somebody tell me what's going on?

283
00:17:48.166 --> 00:17:50.583
Ndumiso. must I repeat myself? Go inside!

284
00:17:51.458 --> 00:17:54.666
Zinhle. go to the cottage.
don't answer your phone and stay there.

285
00:17:54.750 --> 00:17:56.625
Let's take this inside. Let's go!

286
00:17:56.708 --> 00:17:58.625
[in Xhosa] Ndumiso. get in the house.

287
00:17:58.708 --> 00:18:00.041
[Grace in English] Ndumiso. come.

288
00:18:06.583 --> 00:18:07.583
Phila?

289
00:18:07.666 --> 00:18:09.750
[in Sotho] Phila! Talk! What happened?

290
00:18:10.833 --> 00:18:14.500
We were on our way to a warehouse party
that was in the same neighborhood.

291
00:18:14.583 --> 00:18:15.458
Same as what?

292
00:18:15.541 --> 00:18:17.833
Ah. Ndumiso. not now.
This has got nothing to do with...

293
00:18:17.916 --> 00:18:20.458
[in Xhosa] I just want
to know what happened!

294
00:18:20.541 --> 00:18:21.375
Ndumiso!

295
00:18:21.458 --> 00:18:22.875
Are you deaf?

296
00:18:23.375 --> 00:18:24.541
Shut up!

297
00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:28.125
Talk!

298
00:18:29.250 --> 00:18:31.416
[in English]
Uh. we saw the fire in the distance.

299
00:18:31.500 --> 00:18:34.750
I thought it might've been one of ours.
So. we went over there.

300
00:18:34.833 --> 00:18:37.083
and the bleaches
were still intact when we arrived

301
00:18:37.166 --> 00:18:39.208
so I decided it was best
to save some of it.

302
00:18:39.291 --> 00:18:40.875
[in Xhosa] You're an idiot!

303
00:18:40.958 --> 00:18:43.719
[in English] That was your product
I was saving. You know that. right?

304
00:18:43.791 --> 00:18:46.583
The two of you told me
to be more invested in this business.

305
00:18:46.666 --> 00:18:48.833
In fact. you would've
been screaming if I didn't...

306
00:18:48.916 --> 00:18:51.291
You should've turned around
when you realized it was ours!

307
00:18:51.375 --> 00:18:52.583
Is that what I should've done?

308
00:18:52.666 --> 00:18:54.333
I am sorry. all right.

309
00:18:54.416 --> 00:18:56.500
I am so sorry
I don't know what the rules are.

310
00:18:56.583 --> 00:18:58.875
and what it takes to run
a fucking criminal empire

311
00:18:58.958 --> 00:19:00.458
because that's what this is. Okay!

312
00:19:02.041 --> 00:19:03.041
[clicks tongue]

313
00:19:07.958 --> 00:19:10.791
How much did Angela see?

314
00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:13.958
- How much?
- She saw the product.

315
00:19:14.541 --> 00:19:16.375
[in Sotho] Did you tell Zinhle what it is?

316
00:19:16.458 --> 00:19:17.698
[in English] No. of course not.

317
00:19:18.750 --> 00:19:21.291
[sighs] I can still save some of this.

318
00:19:21.375 --> 00:19:23.250
[in Sotho] I have to call Angela.

319
00:19:27.708 --> 00:19:28.833
[Phila sighs]

320
00:19:32.500 --> 00:19:34.500
[shower running]

321
00:19:40.125 --> 00:19:41.875
[door handle rattling]

322
00:19:43.166 --> 00:19:44.583
[knocking on door]

323
00:19:48.583 --> 00:19:50.750
[Ndu in English] Zinhle? Can I come in?

324
00:19:52.875 --> 00:19:53.875
Ndu.

325
00:19:54.666 --> 00:19:56.708
I'm about to take a shower.

326
00:19:56.791 --> 00:19:58.583
[Ndu] Okay. just tell me what happened.

327
00:19:59.250 --> 00:20:02.375
There was a fire. I tried to help Phila...

328
00:20:02.458 --> 00:20:03.916
Can't you ask him?

329
00:20:04.000 --> 00:20:06.208
[Ndu] Yeah. but I just want
to know if you're okay.

330
00:20:06.958 --> 00:20:11.166
I'm fine. Ndu.
I just need to shower and rest. okay.

331
00:20:12.833 --> 00:20:14.416
[Ndu] I'll talk to you in the morning.

332
00:20:21.708 --> 00:20:22.791
[line beeping]

333
00:20:22.875 --> 00:20:23.875
Damn it!

334
00:20:23.958 --> 00:20:24.958
[hangs up]

335
00:20:25.583 --> 00:20:27.208
Kolobe is not answering his phone.

336
00:20:35.833 --> 00:20:37.476
- [answering machine beeps]
- [Kolobe]<i> Hi...</i>

337
00:20:37.500 --> 00:20:38.708
[in Sotho] Oh my goodness.

338
00:20:39.458 --> 00:20:40.916
His phone is off.

339
00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:42.833
- [cell phone chimes]
- [Phila] Oh shit!

340
00:20:42.916 --> 00:20:43.916
Oh.

341
00:20:47.166 --> 00:20:51.083
[woman on TV] <i>Earlier tonight.
new Bhengu Beauty CEO. Phila Bhengu.</i>

342
00:20:51.166 --> 00:20:53.583
<i>and the face of the company.
Zinhle Manzini.</i>

343
00:20:53.666 --> 00:20:57.083
<i>were caught rescuing what
appeared to be illegal skin bleachers</i>

344
00:20:57.166 --> 00:21:00.416
<i>from a burning factory
in the south of Johannesburg.</i>

345
00:21:00.500 --> 00:21:03.583
<i>- Is this a Bhengu factory?
- This is a private property. okay.</i>

346
00:21:03.666 --> 00:21:05.066
[Angela] <i>So it is a Bhengu factory.</i>

347
00:21:05.541 --> 00:21:08.166
[woman] <i>The products in question
bear all the exterior markings</i>

348
00:21:08.250 --> 00:21:10.291
<i>of illegal skin lightening creams.</i>

349
00:21:10.375 --> 00:21:13.125
<i>They have been sent for emergency testing.</i>

350
00:21:13.208 --> 00:21:15.750
<i>If they're found
to contain illegal substances.</i>

351
00:21:15.833 --> 00:21:19.083
<i>the Bhengu Beauty empire
could be dealt a severe blow.</i>

352
00:21:19.166 --> 00:21:22.875
<i>There's been no official statement
or response from Bhengu Beauty.</i>

353
00:21:22.958 --> 00:21:24.958
<i>This is a developing story.</i>

354
00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:27.708
[news theme music playing]

355
00:21:28.583 --> 00:21:30.750
[woman]<i> Dermatologist Dr. Candice Cooper</i>

356
00:21:30.833 --> 00:21:34.083
<i>now joining us to discuss
this very controversial topic.</i>

357
00:21:34.166 --> 00:21:37.166
- Babe.
- Mm. You look nice. Hey.

358
00:21:37.833 --> 00:21:39.666
- Come sit.
- Are you seeing this?

359
00:21:39.750 --> 00:21:40.916
- Gorgeous.
- Look.

360
00:21:41.000 --> 00:21:42.000
What's that?

361
00:21:42.375 --> 00:21:47.250
[Dr. Cooper] <i>Have high amounts of
steroids. hydroquinone. mercury. and lead.</i>

362
00:21:47.333 --> 00:21:49.458
<i>And all of these ingredients...</i>

363
00:21:49.541 --> 00:21:52.625
Apparently Phila was found outside
some skin bleaching factory.

364
00:21:52.708 --> 00:21:53.833
[dialing]

365
00:21:53.916 --> 00:21:57.916
[Dr. Cooper] <i>...scarring.
liver and kidney damage. psychosis.</i>

366
00:21:58.000 --> 00:22:00.750
- Does Bhengu Beauty sell these products?
- [busy signal]

367
00:22:01.916 --> 00:22:02.833
Babe?

368
00:22:02.916 --> 00:22:04.458
[woman] <i>Very serious side effects...</i>

369
00:22:04.541 --> 00:22:06.916
- Linda. you knew about this?
- Yes. I did.

370
00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:09.791
- What?
- [woman] <i>What actually can happen?</i>

371
00:22:09.875 --> 00:22:12.708
[in Xhosa] My father told me
just before he made me CEO.

372
00:22:13.416 --> 00:22:16.125
- [in English] You're okay with this?
- [in Xhosa] What was I to do?

373
00:22:17.875 --> 00:22:19.666
[in English] Wow! [scoffs]

374
00:22:20.375 --> 00:22:22.541
Look. if people want
to poison themselves. then...

375
00:22:24.375 --> 00:22:25.500
[sighs]

376
00:22:29.541 --> 00:22:31.916
<i>...can happen to them.
what the damage can be.</i>

377
00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:35.333
<i>Are we seeing these products
mostly here in South Africa?</i>

378
00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:37.666
Is what's on the news true?

379
00:22:38.875 --> 00:22:42.208
We're releasing a statement
denying any connection to that factory.

380
00:22:42.291 --> 00:22:43.750
[in Xhosa] But is it true or not?

381
00:22:43.833 --> 00:22:45.666
[Don in English] Yes. Ndu. it is true.

382
00:22:45.750 --> 00:22:48.270
Now. will you please shut up
and let us deal with the situation.

383
00:22:48.916 --> 00:22:51.083
- [Ndu] How could you guys do this?
- Um...

384
00:22:51.166 --> 00:22:53.208
I think that there's more.

385
00:22:53.916 --> 00:22:57.500
<i>So. did you know what products
were manufactured in this factory?</i>

386
00:22:58.000 --> 00:22:59.625
[guard] <i>I... No comment.</i>

387
00:23:03.416 --> 00:23:07.833
<i>So in 1990. South Africa became
the first country in the world</i>

388
00:23:07.916 --> 00:23:11.166
<i>to prohibit all cosmetic claims
to skin bleaching.</i>

389
00:23:11.250 --> 00:23:13.000
<i>whitening and/or. lightening.</i>

390
00:23:13.083 --> 00:23:16.125
<i>But. as this burning factory
behind me illustrates.</i>

391
00:23:16.208 --> 00:23:19.250
<i>that the demand for these products.
not only persists</i>

392
00:23:19.333 --> 00:23:20.708
<i>but it's on the rise.</i>

393
00:23:20.791 --> 00:23:23.041
<i>I'm Angela Makwetu reporting live.</i>

394
00:23:31.250 --> 00:23:33.333
[cell phone ringing]

395
00:23:37.666 --> 00:23:38.708
[in Sotho] Hey.

396
00:23:39.416 --> 00:23:41.208
[Bonga] <i>We have a problem. Come now.</i>

397
00:23:41.708 --> 00:23:42.750
What happened?

398
00:23:42.833 --> 00:23:44.708
<i>I need you. Zinhle. Now.</i>

399
00:23:45.583 --> 00:23:46.625
[line beeps off]

400
00:23:49.458 --> 00:23:50.541
Ugh!

401
00:24:05.708 --> 00:24:06.875
[Zinhle groans]

402
00:24:09.041 --> 00:24:10.666
[in Xhosa] Hey. Are you okay?

403
00:24:10.750 --> 00:24:13.125
[in English] No. my head is just...

404
00:24:13.791 --> 00:24:15.375
Let me get you a headache pill.

405
00:24:15.458 --> 00:24:17.083
It's actually a migraine.

406
00:24:17.166 --> 00:24:20.291
It happens with high stress.

407
00:24:21.125 --> 00:24:22.000
Oh!

408
00:24:22.083 --> 00:24:25.208
Yeah. I shouldn't have asked Phila
to go with me yesterday.

409
00:24:25.291 --> 00:24:27.416
No. that has nothing to do with you.

410
00:24:28.958 --> 00:24:30.250
How can I help?

411
00:24:30.333 --> 00:24:32.041
I need to see a doctor.

412
00:24:32.625 --> 00:24:33.875
Okay. I'll get my keys...

413
00:24:33.958 --> 00:24:36.500
- No. I can go on my own.
- No. but...

414
00:24:36.583 --> 00:24:38.983
- [in Xhosa] You can't go on your own.
- [in English] Please.

415
00:24:41.500 --> 00:24:44.000
[sighs] Okay. cool. Um...

416
00:24:44.625 --> 00:24:46.375
Just call me if you need anything.

417
00:24:46.458 --> 00:24:47.875
Yeah. I will.

418
00:24:47.958 --> 00:24:49.041
Please cover for me.

419
00:24:49.125 --> 00:24:51.125
I know we're not supposed
to leave the house.

420
00:24:51.208 --> 00:24:52.333
Don't worry about that.

421
00:24:52.416 --> 00:24:53.625
Okay. thanks.

422
00:24:53.708 --> 00:24:54.750
And Zinhle...

423
00:24:54.833 --> 00:24:55.958
Yeah?

424
00:24:57.208 --> 00:24:59.008
[in Xhosa] We need to talk
when you come back.

425
00:24:59.875 --> 00:25:01.750
[in English] There's a lot
I don't understand.

426
00:25:01.833 --> 00:25:03.208
[Zinhle] Yeah. Mm-hmm.

427
00:25:07.166 --> 00:25:08.291
[phone dialing]

428
00:25:08.375 --> 00:25:10.575
[Kolobe on recording]
<i>Hi. I'm unavailable at the moment.</i>

429
00:25:10.625 --> 00:25:11.708
<i>please leave a message.</i>

430
00:25:13.458 --> 00:25:14.750
[phone dialing]

431
00:25:14.833 --> 00:25:16.833
- [Kolobe] <i>Hi. I'm unavailable...</i>
- Damn it!

432
00:25:16.916 --> 00:25:18.596
[Grace in Sotho]
He'll get back to us soon.

433
00:25:18.625 --> 00:25:21.625
[Don in English]
No. he won't. He's behind this.

434
00:25:23.583 --> 00:25:25.083
And why would he do that?

435
00:25:25.583 --> 00:25:27.125
[Don] Then where the hell is he?

436
00:25:29.083 --> 00:25:30.875
Is there something you need to tell me?

437
00:25:31.958 --> 00:25:32.875
About what?

438
00:25:32.958 --> 00:25:34.166
About the two of you.

439
00:25:35.833 --> 00:25:37.541
First. the guy tells me he's quitting.

440
00:25:37.625 --> 00:25:40.041
Next thing. he disappears
in the middle of a scandal.

441
00:25:41.666 --> 00:25:42.666
What happened?

442
00:25:44.875 --> 00:25:46.083
Tell me!

443
00:25:48.958 --> 00:25:51.166
[in Sotho] He had
started his nonsense again.

444
00:25:52.291 --> 00:25:53.458
You know how he is.

445
00:25:53.541 --> 00:25:56.781
- [in English] Every few years he tries...
- Tries to sleep with you. I know that.

446
00:25:57.208 --> 00:25:59.000
What was so different this time around?

447
00:26:01.708 --> 00:26:03.666
[in Sotho] After your heart attack.

448
00:26:04.708 --> 00:26:06.041
I thought that...

449
00:26:07.791 --> 00:26:08.791
Yeah?

450
00:26:10.750 --> 00:26:13.291
[in English]
He was kind to me when I needed it.

451
00:26:14.083 --> 00:26:15.958
[in Sotho] We met up at the hotel.

452
00:26:16.500 --> 00:26:18.958
I stopped before anything happened. Don.

453
00:26:19.041 --> 00:26:22.208
[in Sotho] I said some harsh things
to him so he'd never try again.

454
00:26:22.291 --> 00:26:24.708
[in English]
I wanted him out of my life for good!

455
00:26:24.791 --> 00:26:25.791
[Don in Sotho] Fool!

456
00:26:25.833 --> 00:26:28.142
Yes. I told him he's a fool
for coming after me all this...

457
00:26:28.166 --> 00:26:30.416
[in English] No! You! You are the fool!

458
00:26:30.500 --> 00:26:31.583
I'm the fool. Don?

459
00:26:31.666 --> 00:26:34.916
You know that Kolobe did everything
because of his feelings for you.

460
00:26:35.000 --> 00:26:37.250
But you had to go and mess it all up!

461
00:26:38.083 --> 00:26:39.333
Don. I'm your wife!

462
00:26:39.416 --> 00:26:40.416
So what!

463
00:26:58.333 --> 00:26:59.583
[whispers] What the fuck!

464
00:27:04.916 --> 00:27:05.958
[door closes]

465
00:27:07.458 --> 00:27:08.625
Zinhle?

466
00:27:08.708 --> 00:27:10.750
[in Sotho] What are we
going to do with a hostage?

467
00:27:10.833 --> 00:27:11.916
And then?

468
00:27:12.708 --> 00:27:13.916
He saw my face.

469
00:27:14.583 --> 00:27:17.166
The place was on fire.

470
00:27:17.250 --> 00:27:18.291
What if...

471
00:27:18.375 --> 00:27:20.625
What if he traced me back to you?

472
00:27:21.583 --> 00:27:24.333
[in English]
He doesn't even know who you are. Bonga.

473
00:27:30.541 --> 00:27:31.875
We can't keep him here.

474
00:27:32.875 --> 00:27:33.875
Zinhle...

475
00:27:34.708 --> 00:27:35.791
Zinhle...

476
00:27:40.291 --> 00:27:41.333
[in Sotho] Wait!

477
00:27:42.333 --> 00:27:43.333
Okay. fine.

478
00:27:46.041 --> 00:27:48.041
[keys jingling]

479
00:27:49.958 --> 00:27:52.000
[Kolobe] I knew you
when you were a little boy.

480
00:27:53.666 --> 00:27:55.625
The scars on your face

481
00:27:58.416 --> 00:28:00.333
[in English] How did you survive the fire?

482
00:28:05.750 --> 00:28:08.125
- [whimpers]
- [flames roaring]

483
00:28:10.083 --> 00:28:11.291
[whimpering]

484
00:28:12.208 --> 00:28:14.000
[children screaming]

485
00:28:31.833 --> 00:28:33.208
[Ndu] Jesus!

486
00:28:39.250 --> 00:28:40.958
- [Phila] Fuck!
- [Grace] And then?

487
00:28:42.208 --> 00:28:43.125
[sighs]

488
00:28:43.208 --> 00:28:45.500
All our products
have been recalled for testing.

489
00:28:45.583 --> 00:28:46.625
For how long?

490
00:28:47.333 --> 00:28:48.333
[Ndu] Hey. man.

491
00:28:48.416 --> 00:28:49.500
[in Xhosa] Look at this.

492
00:28:49.583 --> 00:28:52.000
[in English] Until the bureau
does a complete investigation.

493
00:28:52.083 --> 00:28:53.666
- Do you see this?
- [Phila] Ndu...

494
00:28:53.750 --> 00:28:55.625
The Kenyans have pulled out.

495
00:28:55.708 --> 00:28:58.250
This project is over
and we're hemorrhaging millions!

496
00:28:58.333 --> 00:29:00.583
What about the millions
of people you're harming?

497
00:29:00.666 --> 00:29:02.791
Have you seen what
your products do to people?

498
00:29:02.875 --> 00:29:06.166
Ndumiso! Ndumiso. grow up or get out!

499
00:29:11.625 --> 00:29:12.791
What do we do now?

500
00:29:14.166 --> 00:29:16.458
Someone needs to take the fall.

501
00:29:16.541 --> 00:29:18.125
Okay. who?

502
00:29:19.291 --> 00:29:21.416
I'll try him. Maybe he'll take my call.

503
00:29:22.125 --> 00:29:24.250
Hello. hi. who are we talking about?

504
00:29:24.333 --> 00:29:25.333
[Grace] Kolobe.

505
00:29:27.833 --> 00:29:28.916
It's us or him.

506
00:29:30.375 --> 00:29:31.583
Ndumiso. be useful.

507
00:29:31.666 --> 00:29:34.541
Go and get Zinhle.
She needs to be briefed on what to say.

508
00:29:36.541 --> 00:29:37.541
[in Sotho] Where is she?

509
00:29:38.458 --> 00:29:40.666
- [in English] She's at the doctor.
- She's at the what?

510
00:29:41.958 --> 00:29:43.666
Bhengu Beauty is in crisis!

511
00:29:43.750 --> 00:29:44.958
But she was sick!

512
00:29:45.041 --> 00:29:47.416
- She can't go blabbing to God knows who.
- She was sick.

513
00:29:47.500 --> 00:29:48.541
[in Sotho] Go fetch her.

514
00:29:48.625 --> 00:29:50.458
[in English] Go get her! Go!

515
00:29:54.291 --> 00:29:57.250
[tense music playing]

516
00:30:08.416 --> 00:30:10.416
- [Kolobe on answering machine] <i>Hi...</i>
- [sighs]

517
00:30:10.958 --> 00:30:12.750
- Damn it!
- [phone beeps off]

518
00:30:24.041 --> 00:30:25.250
[Zinhle] Can you stop that?

519
00:30:26.750 --> 00:30:27.750
Please.

520
00:30:32.041 --> 00:30:33.916
[in Sotho] What are we going to do?

521
00:30:35.250 --> 00:30:36.250
Hmm?

522
00:30:38.250 --> 00:30:40.125
[in English] You're not gonna like it.

523
00:30:41.916 --> 00:30:42.916
[in Sotho] It's risky.

524
00:30:43.500 --> 00:30:46.833
But if we pull it off
then it's over for Don and Grace.

525
00:30:49.375 --> 00:30:50.958
[in English] I hear you. Zinhle.

526
00:30:51.916 --> 00:30:53.958
[Zinhle] You just need to follow my lead.

527
00:30:54.875 --> 00:30:56.166
[in Sotho] Trust me.

528
00:31:04.416 --> 00:31:07.083
[Angela in English] <i>A burning building
s a news item. Mr. Bhengu.</i>

529
00:31:07.166 --> 00:31:10.750
<i>- Is this a Bhengu factory?</i>
- [Phila] <i>This is a private property. okay.</i>

530
00:31:13.333 --> 00:31:14.333
Baby.

531
00:31:15.291 --> 00:31:19.166
Look. I'm... sorry for earlier.

532
00:31:21.250 --> 00:31:25.791
I know that those products
are dangerous and unethical. but

533
00:31:26.458 --> 00:31:27.791
you know with Dad.

534
00:31:28.500 --> 00:31:31.416
Just... all that mattered
was impressing him. okay.

535
00:31:32.000 --> 00:31:35.083
I just don't want
Don's shadow hanging over us.

536
00:31:35.166 --> 00:31:36.916
I know. okay. Me neither.

537
00:31:37.000 --> 00:31:39.916
Then let's stop keeping up
with what's going on with that family.

538
00:31:41.000 --> 00:31:43.500
Honey. we need space.

539
00:31:43.583 --> 00:31:45.291
mentally and physically.

540
00:31:45.375 --> 00:31:46.625
Okay.

541
00:31:47.875 --> 00:31:49.000
- Come here.
- Thank you.

542
00:31:49.083 --> 00:31:50.125
Uh-huh. [kisses]

543
00:32:01.166 --> 00:32:02.166
Zinhle?

544
00:32:03.916 --> 00:32:05.375
[in Sotho] What are you doing here?

545
00:32:07.083 --> 00:32:08.208
What's going on here?

546
00:32:09.208 --> 00:32:10.375
[Zinhle] Hello. Calvin.

547
00:32:11.666 --> 00:32:13.166
[in English] Or should I say <i>malume?</i>

548
00:32:14.333 --> 00:32:15.958
[in Sotho] This is my brother.

549
00:32:16.041 --> 00:32:18.375
I was also at the house.

550
00:32:19.875 --> 00:32:21.601
[in English]
But you're the face of Bhengu...

551
00:32:21.625 --> 00:32:24.125
[in Sotho]
She'd wash off chemicals you used on me.

552
00:32:25.291 --> 00:32:28.708
Do you remember the day
Don Bhengu burnt me?

553
00:32:32.250 --> 00:32:33.250
Do you remember?

554
00:32:35.458 --> 00:32:37.000
Do you remember?!

555
00:32:43.041 --> 00:32:47.000
- [Kolobe] What about the fire?
- [Zinhle] We managed... to escape.

556
00:32:48.208 --> 00:32:51.208
Me. my brother and my sister.

557
00:32:54.375 --> 00:32:56.250
Our sister. Amahle.

558
00:32:58.166 --> 00:33:01.625
She died in this very room.
seven months ago.

559
00:33:05.458 --> 00:33:06.875
[in English] Liver cancer.

560
00:33:08.166 --> 00:33:10.666
[in Sotho] All because of your chemicals.

561
00:33:13.666 --> 00:33:15.250
We escaped the fire.

562
00:33:17.708 --> 00:33:21.583
But we never survived what you did to us.

563
00:33:23.458 --> 00:33:24.583
My brother's body.

564
00:33:26.250 --> 00:33:27.916
My face.

565
00:33:29.041 --> 00:33:30.583
My sister's life.

566
00:33:33.083 --> 00:33:34.166
[Kolobe] I'm sorry.

567
00:33:36.416 --> 00:33:37.416
I'm sorry.

568
00:33:38.333 --> 00:33:41.000
[Zinhle] If you really mean it. help us.

569
00:33:42.958 --> 00:33:48.625
Help us show the world
what Don and Grace did to us.

570
00:33:57.625 --> 00:33:58.791
[in English] I can't.

571
00:34:06.250 --> 00:34:07.416
[yells] No!

572
00:34:36.750 --> 00:34:38.708
- [sniffles]
- [in English] It's okay.

573
00:34:40.166 --> 00:34:41.416
I got you.

574
00:34:42.375 --> 00:34:48.250
<i>♪ I don't know if I ever really told you ♪</i>

575
00:34:48.333 --> 00:34:50.375
<i>♪ I need you ♪</i>

576
00:34:50.458 --> 00:34:54.083
["Be Like Home" by David O'Dowda playing]

577
00:34:55.000 --> 00:34:59.041
<i>♪ I can't breathe ♪</i>

578
00:34:59.125 --> 00:35:00.583
[Kolobe in Sotho] It's okay.

579
00:35:00.666 --> 00:35:02.000
You'll heal.

580
00:35:04.166 --> 00:35:07.208
[Zinhle in English]
<i>You were a parent to us at that place.</i>

581
00:35:08.458 --> 00:35:10.333
The closest thing to a father.

582
00:35:10.916 --> 00:35:13.041
[Kolobe] No. I wasn't.

583
00:35:15.041 --> 00:35:18.041
[in Sotho] Don and Grace came once a week...

584
00:35:18.125 --> 00:35:20.708
[in English] ...to put
that cream on us. But you...

585
00:35:21.458 --> 00:35:23.625
[in Sotho] But you were there every day.

586
00:35:24.583 --> 00:35:27.541
You used to bathe us.
You'd feed us and put us to sleep.

587
00:35:27.625 --> 00:35:29.041
[in English] In your own way...

588
00:35:29.125 --> 00:35:30.458
[in Sotho] You cared for us.

589
00:35:35.375 --> 00:35:38.583
[in English] Do the right thing. Kolobe.
Help us get justice.

590
00:35:38.666 --> 00:35:40.041
[in Sotho] I'm begging you.

591
00:35:51.083 --> 00:35:53.083
[tense music plays]

592
00:36:04.208 --> 00:36:06.333
[in English]
If you know what's good for you...

593
00:36:07.583 --> 00:36:08.666
[in Sotho] You'll help us.

594
00:36:08.750 --> 00:36:10.291
[Kolobe in English] Or what?

595
00:36:10.375 --> 00:36:11.666
[in Sotho] Let me go.

596
00:36:12.375 --> 00:36:15.958
- [in English] Don and Grace'll never know.
- [cell phone ringing]

597
00:36:17.333 --> 00:36:18.375
[Zinhle] <i>Hello.</i>

598
00:36:18.958 --> 00:36:20.875
Hey. are you at the doctor?

599
00:36:20.958 --> 00:36:24.458
Yeah. sorry I'm running late.
Is everything okay there?

600
00:36:24.541 --> 00:36:27.541
Everyone is coming up with lies
to make this thing go away.

601
00:36:29.666 --> 00:36:30.666
[mutters]

602
00:36:31.083 --> 00:36:32.208
What lies?

603
00:36:32.875 --> 00:36:36.458
[Ndu] <i>Can you believe they're trying to
pin it on the guy that runs the factory?</i>

604
00:36:38.125 --> 00:36:40.458
Are you okay to drive back?
I can come fetch you.

605
00:36:40.541 --> 00:36:43.000
Yeah. I'm almost done. Thank you.

606
00:36:44.208 --> 00:36:45.625
[phone beeps]

607
00:36:50.708 --> 00:36:54.625
[woman] <i>The factory in question contains
illegal skin lightening creams.</i>

608
00:36:54.708 --> 00:36:59.041
<i>and registered as a textile factory
owned by Mr. Calvin Mamabolo.</i>

609
00:36:59.125 --> 00:37:01.125
<i>A warrant for his arrest has been issued...</i>

610
00:37:01.208 --> 00:37:03.434
[Zinhle in Sotho] Don and Grace'll
throw you to the dogs.

611
00:37:03.458 --> 00:37:05.125
[woman] <i>...contact their nearest police.</i>

612
00:37:05.208 --> 00:37:07.208
[Zinhle in Sotho] Are you still
going to help them?

613
00:37:08.125 --> 00:37:10.125
Unlock his phone and let's call Grace.

614
00:37:11.791 --> 00:37:12.958
What's the PIN?

615
00:37:13.833 --> 00:37:14.958
PIN!

616
00:37:15.833 --> 00:37:16.916
[clicks tongue]

617
00:37:18.375 --> 00:37:19.416
[phone clicks]

618
00:37:20.125 --> 00:37:21.333
[Bonga scoffs]

619
00:37:24.875 --> 00:37:25.875
[sighs]

620
00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:34.250
[tones beeping]

621
00:37:35.166 --> 00:37:36.500
[line ringing]

622
00:37:41.000 --> 00:37:43.083
[cell phone ringing]

623
00:37:44.291 --> 00:37:45.375
Calvin?

624
00:37:47.291 --> 00:37:48.416
<i>Calvin?</i>

625
00:37:51.250 --> 00:37:52.250
<i>Calvin?</i>

626
00:37:55.833 --> 00:37:56.833
[in English] I'm here.

627
00:37:57.416 --> 00:37:58.875
Oh. thank God.

628
00:37:59.500 --> 00:38:00.500
[in Sotho] Are you okay?

629
00:38:00.583 --> 00:38:01.666
[in English] <i>I'm fine.</i>

630
00:38:03.750 --> 00:38:05.590
[in Sotho]
Have you seen what's been happening?

631
00:38:06.125 --> 00:38:07.205
[in English] It's terrible.

632
00:38:08.625 --> 00:38:09.625
I know.

633
00:38:10.000 --> 00:38:12.916
[Grace in Sotho] <i>You're the only one
who can make this go away.</i>

634
00:38:13.750 --> 00:38:14.958
[in English]<i> We need you.</i>

635
00:38:15.041 --> 00:38:17.916
[dramatic music playing]

636
00:38:28.333 --> 00:38:29.601
[in Sotho] Don will make sure...

637
00:38:29.625 --> 00:38:31.351
[in English] ...you don't spend one night...

638
00:38:31.375 --> 00:38:32.583
[in Sotho] ...in jail.

639
00:38:33.875 --> 00:38:35.583
[in English] The docket will disappear.

640
00:38:39.500 --> 00:38:40.541
Calvin?

641
00:38:43.291 --> 00:38:44.291
Okay.

642
00:38:46.708 --> 00:38:47.708
[phone beeps off]

643
00:38:48.250 --> 00:38:49.500
What's your answer?

644
00:38:56.333 --> 00:38:58.458
[somber music plays]

645
00:39:02.250 --> 00:39:03.890
[Phila] <i>What the hell are you doing here?</i>

646
00:39:03.916 --> 00:39:05.750
[Angela] <i>A burning building
is a news item.</i>

647
00:39:05.833 --> 00:39:07.833
Babe? What do you think?

648
00:39:07.916 --> 00:39:10.166
- It's gorgeous.
- Linda. what the fuck?

649
00:39:11.041 --> 00:39:15.666
Please. just watch it. okay?
I need you. It's Phila at the factory.

650
00:39:16.333 --> 00:39:19.666
<i>- Phila...</i>
- Look. Zinhle pushes the box.

651
00:39:19.750 --> 00:39:22.208
Now you're blaming Zinhle
for something she didn't do!

652
00:39:22.291 --> 00:39:23.666
I just don't trust her.

653
00:39:23.750 --> 00:39:25.583
You promised you'd stop obsessing over...

654
00:39:25.666 --> 00:39:26.750
This is not easy!

655
00:39:26.833 --> 00:39:29.083
You're dragging her
into your fucking daddy issues!

656
00:39:31.666 --> 00:39:33.125
I need you to stop seeing her.

657
00:39:33.208 --> 00:39:34.625
- Excuse me?
- You heard me.

658
00:39:34.708 --> 00:39:35.583
[scoffs]

659
00:39:35.666 --> 00:39:37.166
Just until I can trust her.

660
00:39:38.500 --> 00:39:39.666
Linda...

661
00:39:39.750 --> 00:39:41.875
I'm obsessing over my family. right?

662
00:39:41.958 --> 00:39:43.333
Stop being friends with her.

663
00:39:46.166 --> 00:39:47.791
You know. you're... [sighs]

664
00:39:48.791 --> 00:39:50.416
You're just like your dad.

665
00:40:03.375 --> 00:40:04.833
[keypad beeping]

666
00:40:05.708 --> 00:40:07.791
Hey. Um. listen. friend.

667
00:40:07.875 --> 00:40:12.458
Do you... Do you have the guest list
of the last Emerald party for me. please?

668
00:40:14.041 --> 00:40:16.625
[sighs] Thank you. Perfect. Right.

669
00:40:17.541 --> 00:40:18.541
[phone beeps off]

670
00:40:35.583 --> 00:40:39.083
[Zinhle in Sotho]
Grace just sent a copy of your statement.

671
00:40:39.166 --> 00:40:40.791
[in English] For the press conference.

672
00:40:40.875 --> 00:40:42.333
[in Sotho] Do you want to see it?

673
00:40:42.416 --> 00:40:43.500
[Kolobe] There's no need.

674
00:40:43.583 --> 00:40:45.083
I know what it will say.

675
00:40:47.791 --> 00:40:50.875
[in English] I'll reveal myself
after you tell everyone about the tests.

676
00:40:52.375 --> 00:40:53.958
Um... [clears throat]

677
00:40:54.708 --> 00:40:57.041
[in Sotho]
What will you do if they deny it?

678
00:40:58.000 --> 00:41:00.875
[in English] I've got documents
at my house that implicate them.

679
00:41:01.458 --> 00:41:03.375
We just need to go pick them up.

680
00:41:03.458 --> 00:41:04.541
Oh. Um...

681
00:41:24.166 --> 00:41:25.916
[in Sotho] Don't let us down again.

682
00:41:26.000 --> 00:41:27.625
[tense music builds]

683
00:41:39.416 --> 00:41:41.750
[Ndu in English] I saw you come in.
We really need to talk.

684
00:41:41.833 --> 00:41:43.458
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

685
00:41:45.458 --> 00:41:47.333
Why do you keep avoiding me?

686
00:41:48.875 --> 00:41:50.375
You'd never understand.

687
00:41:50.458 --> 00:41:51.916
Okay. just try me.

688
00:41:53.458 --> 00:41:55.083
Trust me. okay.

689
00:41:55.708 --> 00:41:57.625
Everything will make sense tomorrow.

690
00:41:58.666 --> 00:41:59.666
I promise.

691
00:42:02.708 --> 00:42:03.708
[Ndu sighs]

692
00:42:13.208 --> 00:42:15.250
[in Sotho] Phila. where's Zinhle?

693
00:42:15.333 --> 00:42:16.750
[in English] She's coming.

694
00:42:16.833 --> 00:42:17.958
[in Sotho] And Kolobe?

695
00:42:18.916 --> 00:42:20.375
He'll meet us at the hall.

696
00:42:21.291 --> 00:42:22.458
[Zinhle] I'm ready.

697
00:42:22.541 --> 00:42:24.500
Grace. I'm sorry for leaving yesterday.

698
00:42:24.583 --> 00:42:26.583
[in English] No.
we can deal with that later.

699
00:42:26.666 --> 00:42:27.541
[in Sotho] Let's go.

700
00:42:27.625 --> 00:42:28.945
[in Xhosa] Where is Zinhle going?

701
00:42:29.000 --> 00:42:30.760
[in English]
She has nothing to do with this.

702
00:42:30.791 --> 00:42:33.476
[in Sotho] Zinhle works for us.
in case you forgot. Let's go. Zinhle.

703
00:42:33.500 --> 00:42:36.184
- [in English] Fine. Then I'm coming with.
- You don't have to do that.

704
00:42:36.208 --> 00:42:37.541
Someone has to have your back.

705
00:42:44.625 --> 00:42:46.333
[tires squealing]

706
00:42:47.333 --> 00:42:49.333
[brakes squeaking]

707
00:42:59.875 --> 00:43:01.125
[in Sotho] Are you ready?

708
00:43:03.375 --> 00:43:04.375
[in English] Yeah.

709
00:43:08.458 --> 00:43:09.958
[in Sotho] Tell me something.

710
00:43:15.375 --> 00:43:16.416
[in English] Why?

711
00:43:17.916 --> 00:43:19.583
[in Sotho] Why did you do it?

712
00:43:22.541 --> 00:43:25.416
Why are you still in touch with them?

713
00:43:25.500 --> 00:43:27.500
Why are you still in business with them?

714
00:43:31.958 --> 00:43:32.958
Love.

715
00:43:43.500 --> 00:43:45.500
[tense music playing]

716
00:43:54.083 --> 00:43:57.833
[indistinct conversations]

717
00:44:00.833 --> 00:44:03.125
[camera shutters clicking]

718
00:44:03.208 --> 00:44:05.125
[reporters clamoring]

719
00:44:08.708 --> 00:44:10.083
[in English] Take your seats!

720
00:44:10.166 --> 00:44:12.208
- [overlapping chatter]
- Take your seats!

721
00:44:22.166 --> 00:44:25.500
[PR woman] Ladies and gentlemen.
please settle down. Take your seats.

722
00:44:26.916 --> 00:44:28.500
- Thank you for coming.
- [phone chimes]

723
00:44:28.583 --> 00:44:31.083
[PR woman]
This is how today's program will go.

724
00:44:33.000 --> 00:44:34.791
Mr. Calvin Mamabolo

725
00:44:35.708 --> 00:44:37.375
is going to set the record straight.

726
00:44:37.458 --> 00:44:38.541
[cell phone chimes]

727
00:44:47.875 --> 00:44:52.500
[PR woman] After that. Mr. Phila Bhengu
will to make an official statement.

728
00:44:54.125 --> 00:44:55.208
[grunts]

729
00:44:57.333 --> 00:44:59.166
- [groans]
- [Don's phone chimes]

730
00:44:59.250 --> 00:45:02.708
[PR woman] And if you've submitted
anything. it will be answered. Thank you.

731
00:45:10.541 --> 00:45:12.708
[reporters] Mr. Bhengu!

732
00:45:12.791 --> 00:45:14.375
Where are you going?

733
00:45:29.208 --> 00:45:30.750
[Bonga] Shit.

734
00:45:34.541 --> 00:45:35.583
[chimes]

735
00:45:38.333 --> 00:45:39.250
Hey.

736
00:45:39.333 --> 00:45:40.625
Are you okay?

737
00:45:40.708 --> 00:45:42.791
Yeah. I... I need the bathroom.

738
00:45:44.958 --> 00:45:46.958
[indistinct chatter]

739
00:45:51.125 --> 00:45:52.541
He's clearly not coming.

740
00:45:53.916 --> 00:45:55.500
It's time for your statement.

741
00:46:01.625 --> 00:46:03.083
[clears throat]

742
00:46:04.250 --> 00:46:08.291
Ahem. Ladies and gentlemen.
thank you for your time.

743
00:46:10.291 --> 00:46:12.791
An unfortunate incident occurred recently

744
00:46:12.875 --> 00:46:15.458
involving myself as
the CEO of Bhengu Beauty.

745
00:46:15.541 --> 00:46:19.875
as well as Zinhle Manzini.
the face of the company.

746
00:46:20.625 --> 00:46:21.791
[truck engine starts]

747
00:46:23.000 --> 00:46:26.166
[Phila] <i>I'd like to state here today
that Bhengu Beauty</i>

748
00:46:26.250 --> 00:46:30.000
<i>denies any and all knowledge
of these products.</i>

749
00:46:30.500 --> 00:46:33.916
<i>The factory in question was leased
to a friend to manufacture furniture.</i>

750
00:46:34.000 --> 00:46:35.791
<i>Someone we considered family.</i>

751
00:46:36.375 --> 00:46:39.875
Mr. Calvin Mamabolo decided to manufacture

752
00:46:39.958 --> 00:46:42.500
skin bleaching products
without our knowledge.

753
00:46:42.583 --> 00:46:44.666
Something we consider a betrayal.

754
00:46:45.375 --> 00:46:49.416
And when we gave him the chance to explain
his actions. instead. he disappeared.

755
00:46:54.125 --> 00:46:55.333
[tires squealing]

756
00:46:55.416 --> 00:46:56.934
- [in Sotho] Don kidnapped Kolobe.
- What?

757
00:46:56.958 --> 00:46:59.000
There's a tablet in there.

758
00:46:59.083 --> 00:47:00.416
What am I looking for?

759
00:47:00.500 --> 00:47:02.708
We're tracking Kolobe's location.

760
00:47:02.791 --> 00:47:05.000
I'm tracking his phone.

761
00:47:05.083 --> 00:47:10.208
[Phila in English] Ladies and gentlemen.
we ask that you put your trust back in us.

762
00:47:11.291 --> 00:47:16.000
All of our products have been tested
and all of them are 100% safe.

763
00:47:16.083 --> 00:47:19.375
Bhengu Beauty will
always protect its customers

764
00:47:19.458 --> 00:47:21.833
because our beauty is real.

765
00:47:24.083 --> 00:47:25.208
That's all. thank you.

766
00:47:25.291 --> 00:47:26.291
[woman] Mr. Bhengu!

767
00:47:26.375 --> 00:47:29.500
[reporters clamoring]

768
00:47:29.583 --> 00:47:31.666
[camera shutters clicking]

769
00:47:34.375 --> 00:47:35.458
[mouthing] Well done.

770
00:47:44.375 --> 00:47:45.708
[Zinhle] That's where we are.

771
00:47:45.791 --> 00:47:48.000
- [Bonga in Sotho] Where do we go?
- This way.

772
00:47:51.541 --> 00:47:52.583
Faster.

773
00:47:52.666 --> 00:47:53.666
[Bonga] Okay. okay.

774
00:47:56.458 --> 00:47:57.500
[Zinhle] Over there.

775
00:47:59.916 --> 00:48:01.541
There's no one inside.

776
00:48:05.541 --> 00:48:09.291
His location says he's 500m
east behind the building.

777
00:48:14.166 --> 00:48:16.083
Zinhle. wait. Whoa. Zinhle!

778
00:48:25.291 --> 00:48:26.375
[in English] Why now?

779
00:48:30.666 --> 00:48:31.666
Huh?

780
00:48:32.208 --> 00:48:34.291
Answer me. why now?

781
00:48:34.875 --> 00:48:36.125
[Kolobe] It was time.

782
00:48:36.208 --> 00:48:38.458
[Don] You only had to stick to the plan.

783
00:48:38.541 --> 00:48:40.875
Yes. Stick to the plan
and be your servant.

784
00:48:40.958 --> 00:48:42.500
[in Sotho] For the rest of my life.

785
00:48:42.583 --> 00:48:44.458
[in English] You never used to mind.

786
00:48:44.541 --> 00:48:46.501
[Kolobe]
The world needs to know what we did. Don.

787
00:48:46.541 --> 00:48:49.083
Because my wife
wouldn't want to leave me for you?

788
00:48:49.875 --> 00:48:50.708
Pathetic!

789
00:48:50.791 --> 00:48:52.708
[Kolobe] We have done enough harm.

790
00:48:52.791 --> 00:48:54.471
[in Sotho] If this is my fate.
I accept it.

791
00:48:54.541 --> 00:48:58.208
- [in English] Just give me the gun.
- [in Sotho] But yours. yours is coming.

792
00:49:01.750 --> 00:49:03.833
[gunshot echoes]

793
00:49:14.375 --> 00:49:20.250
<i>♪ I don't know if I ever really told you ♪</i>

794
00:49:20.333 --> 00:49:22.333
<i>♪ I need you ♪</i>

795
00:49:26.958 --> 00:49:33.166
<i>♪ I can't breathe ♪</i>

796
00:49:34.333 --> 00:49:37.791
<i>♪ Only sojourn ♪</i>

797
00:49:41.791 --> 00:49:44.291
<i>♪ Make me a wish ♪</i>

798
00:49:45.416 --> 00:49:50.333
<i>♪ Keep me by your side ♪</i>

799
00:49:52.416 --> 00:49:55.500
<i>♪ It'll be like home ♪</i>

800
00:49:57.333 --> 00:50:00.250
[suspenseful music playing]

801
00:50:01.305 --> 00:51:01.552
Do you want subtitles for any video?
